    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate focusing on high-ceiling leadoff threats and situational favorable matchups. **Brice Turang** (63.18) and **James Wood** (66.66) are our offensive anchors, both benefiting from the prime #1 lineup spot and favorable projections against pitchers with exploitable delivery tempos. **Brice Turang** is a priority start because his 87% stolen base success rate aligns perfectly with a matchup against Meibrys Kelly, whose slower delivery facilitates our league-wide focus on SB acquisition. Similarly, **Corbin Carroll** (67.44) headlines our outfield despite a 50% hold rate from his opponent, as his elite xwOBA remains the most reliable engine for R and HR production. **Seiya Suzuki** (65.21) earns a high score today, largely because he draws a massive +19% SP skill boost against Walker Buehler\u2019s projected 5.19 xERA, providing the best value-to-matchup profile in the OF depth chart.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involves the exclusion of **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (53.05). While he remains a core component of our speed-first strategy, he was benched in favor of higher-efficiency hitters like **Vinnie Pasquantino** (65.82) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (59.59), who benefit significantly from park factors. **Tyler Soderstrom** specifically benefits from a +10% park boost today, allowing him to edge out more aggressive options against Kris Bubic. We must monitor the lineup statuses for **Luis Campusano**, **Max Muncy**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino**; if any drop significantly in the batting order from our assumed placements, their scores will compress toward the marginal tier. We are avoiding exposure to deGrom, which is the primary reason **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Jose Caballero** were left on the bench; even with their high speed potential, the SP skill penalty attached to deGrom effectively renders them below our operational floor today.",
